In the Matter of Manuel P. ASENSIO, Appellant,
v.
Adetokunbo FASANYA, Respondent. 2018-151
New York County Index No. 155833/17 Court of Appeals of New York. Decided February 15, 2018 On the Court's own motion, appeal dismissed, without costs, upon the ground that the order appealed from does not finally determine the proceeding within the meaning of the Constitution. Motion for leave to appeal dismissed upon the ground that the order sought to be appealed from does not finally determine the proceeding within the meaning of the Constitution. Chief Judge DiFiore took no part.
